minism or external dependency.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.8,"Integration":0.15,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The full pipeline — dispatching to all three reviewers, collecting results, merging into a unified report — completes correctly for a real contract without losing any individual reviewer's findings.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Testing the orchestration (dispatch, parallel collection, merge without loss) requires multiple modules wired together. Unit tests of individual merge logic (Behavior 4) don't exercise the dispatch/collection/coordination flow. Integration level with mocked reviewers catches data loss, race conditions, and orchestration failures. The core failure mode—'a reviewer's output is lost in collection or dispatch fails'—is deterministic in the orchestration layer and doesn't require real reviewers, though real reviewers (Workflow) would provide stronger end-to-end verification.","test_description":"Integration test: Mock all three reviewers to return realistic, diverse outputs (varying numbers of findings, different clause types). Run the full orchestration pipeline on realistic contracts. Verify: all three reviewers are dispatched, all outputs collected without loss, results merged with no findings dropped, parallel dispatch completes without race conditions, unified report contains all findings with correct attribution. Test with contracts of varying complexity. Verify output schema validity.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"At Integration level, we test orchestration—dispatch, collection, merge—with mocked reviewers on realistic data. Self-check: Could a Unit test catch 'lost findings in collection'? No, needs full orchestration flow. Could a higher level (Workflow with real reviewers) catch something Integration misses? Yes—unexpected reviewer failures or schema mismatches in real outputs—but Integration is sufficient for the stated behavior.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.68,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.08,"Workflow":0.14}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13585,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":13585},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2e9b04ed-35c6-4a6c-bcbc-b81bf3b38e6a","uuid":"87342631-2d2a-4fd2-aa97-0aeddb9aaec0"}
